DisplayText: Through the rough rural roads, Theodore thoroughly thought about the weather. Was it truly a terrible Thursday, or just a slightly turbulent 1? Though the wind whistled wildly, the Willow trees wavered without worry. Meanwhile, a peculiar pheasant perched peacefully on the fence, unfazed by the chaotic chorus of chirping crickets. Surely, Theodore sighed, this tongue-twisting turmoil of tricky words will train my tongue to talk tidily.
